						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of sheep (or cows) by Nāraṇaṉ Poliñjāṉ, a resident of Jayaṅgoṇḍa-śōḻapuram in Valla-nāḍu, for the merit of his wife, for burning a lamp in the temple of Karumāṇikka-Āḻvār at Teṉ Tirumāliruñjōlai in Kīḻkaḷakkūṟṟam which is stated to be a sub-division of Muḍigoṇḍaśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu, which formed again a division of Rājarāja-Pāṇḍināḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
